history.text: Did you think this movie was as bad as I did?
yes, probably the worst movie of the year.
why didn't you like this movie?
There wasn't any reason to care about who won or lost.
ok. that makes sense
I thought the story line was very contrived
Batman and Superman were both unlikable and Lex Luthor was bad.
Yeah I agree completely.
Ben Affleck might have been the worst possible choice to  play batman
They spent the entire movie building up this Batman vs Superman fight and then they reconcile just because their moms have the same name?
I actually liked Affleck.
I thought the only bright spot in the movie was diane lane's portrayal of martha Kent. She put a twist on the character that I didn't anticipate
she was able to portray different levels to the character. if she had had a bigger role in the movie I think it would have improved the overall impression of the movie
what did you think of gal gadot in this movie?
Her limited screen time was good, but Wonder Woman being in the movie was pointless other than to tease the Justice League movie. Same with the Flash.
i agree completely. I think that was their only objective
She's wonderful though, the full length WW movie is actually the best thing DC has put out sans the Nolan trilogy.
yeah. I'm really not surprised by the score this movie got on rotten tomatoes
Not at all, it's a pretty accurate representation of the film I think.
What do you think of Henry Cavill as Superman?
As I was watching the film I couldn't help but think that ben affleck must not have prepared at all for this role. I think he just showed up to shoot the scenes and that's it
Henry cavill was average at best. I can't say i was impressed by him , but at the same time, he was fine.
Agreed. He's just kind of there. Not great, not bad, nothing to write home about.
And that's just not enough for a leading actor in a film.
right. he really needs to be something special if he's going to be the lead
who do you think should have gotten that lead role?
That's a tough choice. I'm not a particularly huge fan of the character to begin with to be honest.
I think the real problem is the writing though.
right. but there's no actor you think could make the character more interesting?
Cavill could do better with decent writing I think.
That's honestly the main issue.
fair enough
Now i'm all alone.
